namespace kindergarten_garden {

std::map<std::string, std::vector<std::string>> plants(const std::string& diagram) {
    // Split the diagram into two rows
    std::istringstream iss(diagram);
    std::string row1, row2;
    std::getline(iss, row1);
    std::getline(iss, row2);
    
    // Remove any carriage return characters if present (for cross-platform compatibility)
    row1.erase(std::remove(row1.begin(), row1.end(), '\r'), row1.end());
    row2.erase(std::remove(row2.begin(), row2.end(), '\r'), row2.end());
    row1.erase(std::remove(row1.begin(), row1.end(), '\n'), row1.end());
    row2.erase(std::remove(row2.begin(), row2.end(), '\n'), row2.end());
    
    // List of children in order
    const std::vector<std::string> children = {
        "Alice", "Bob", "Charlie", "David",
        "Eve", "Fred", "Ginny", "Harriet",
        "Ileana", "Joseph", "Kincaid", "Larry"
    };
    
    std::map<std::string, std::vector<std::string>> result;
    
    for (std::size_t i = 0; i < children.size(); ++i) {
        const std::string& child = children[i];
        // Each child gets two plants per row, at positions 2*i and 2*i +1
        std::size_t pos1 = 2 * i;
        std::size_t pos2 = (2 * i) + 1;
        
        // Get plant codes from both rows
        // Ensure positions are within bounds
        if (pos1 >= row1.size() || pos2 >= row1.size() || 
            pos1 >= row2.size() || pos2 >= row2.size()) {
            continue;
        }
        
        char codes[4] = {
            row1[pos1], 
            row1[pos2], 
            row2[pos1], 
            row2[pos2]
        };
        
        // Convert codes to plant names
        std::vector<std::string> child_plants;
        for (std::size_t j = 0; j < 4; ++j) {
            switch (codes[j]) {
                case 'G': child_plants.push_back("grass"); break;
                case 'C': child_plants.push_back("clover"); break;
                case 'R': child_plants.push_back("radishes"); break;
                case 'V': child_plants.push_back("violets"); break;
                default: break;
            }
        }
        result[child] = child_plants;
    }
    
    return result;
}

}  // namespace kindergarten_garden
